132
00:13:45,710 --> 00:13:48,129
<i>and Kim Gang-hui and Lim So-yeon
from room 206.</i>

133
00:13:48,212 --> 00:13:51,340
<i>Yeong-ro received a necklace as a gift
from an unnamed man who was</i>

134
00:13:51,424 --> 00:13:52,925
<i>her partner at the Open House.</i>

135
00:13:53,384 --> 00:13:54,969
<i>They must be seeing each other.</i>

136
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:57,346
The girl who treated me?

137
00:13:58,389 --> 00:14:02,059
<i>I heard the ANSP director's son is dead.
What if they try to retaliate against us?</i>

138
00:14:07,565 --> 00:14:09,233
<i>Did you forget about the instructions?</i>

139
00:14:10,151 --> 00:14:12,695
But they were given before his death.

140
00:14:13,070 --> 00:14:16,365
<i>I'm at Hosu University where
the armed spies are holding people hostage</i>

141
00:14:16,449 --> 00:14:19,285
<i>after escaping the ANSP surveillance.</i>

142
00:14:19,368 --> 00:14:21,162
<i>The university is closed to the public</i>

143
00:14:21,245 --> 00:14:24,498
<i>including its students, and the police
special forces have been sent in.</i>

144
00:14:24,582 --> 00:14:29,045
<i>ANSP has camped in front of the dorm
and taken control of the scene--</i>

145
00:14:32,173 --> 00:14:35,885
Set a booby trap on the cafeteria windows
and put an extra bomb.

146
00:14:36,969 --> 00:14:38,888
<i>A bomb?</i>

147
00:14:39,263 --> 00:14:41,682
If they try to deceive us again,

148
00:14:44,268 --> 00:14:45,519
I'll push the button.

149
00:16:06,308 --> 00:16:08,853
Talk about bad timing.

150
00:16:09,562 --> 00:16:11,230
If only you'd come in a bit later.

151
00:16:12,773 --> 00:16:13,816
Turn around.

152
00:16:40,051 --> 00:16:41,177
That…

153
00:16:41,844 --> 00:16:43,846
Why is that…

154
00:17:02,198 --> 00:17:04,366
You know I have
a detonator in my pocket, right?

155
00:17:05,076 --> 00:17:06,994
Don't try anything funny.

156
00:17:07,870 --> 00:17:09,330
Will you blow everyone up?

157
00:17:10,414 --> 00:17:13,834
You know Lee Seong-jo, right? The one
who came to assassinate the president.

158
00:17:14,919 --> 00:17:18,172
He fell in love with someone in the South
and is living happily.

159
00:17:20,299 --> 00:17:23,427
Don't you want to live here
with someone you love, like him?

160
00:17:29,391 --> 00:17:32,269
If you want to live happily
with that woman, don't do anything stupid.

161
00:17:33,104 --> 00:17:34,313
I won't let it slide twice.

162
00:17:35,815 --> 00:17:37,942
"That woman"? Who?

163
00:17:39,276 --> 00:17:43,906
Oh, her? She's just
one of my subordinates. Nothing more.

164
00:17:44,740 --> 00:17:46,450
Just colleagues.

165
00:18:02,174 --> 00:18:03,259
Go in.

166
00:18:31,495 --> 00:18:32,705
How is she?

167
00:18:32,788 --> 00:18:35,124
I gave her a tranquilizer,

168
00:18:35,207 --> 00:18:37,793
so she'll be fine after some sleep.

169
00:18:50,014 --> 00:18:51,724
Can we have a word for a minute?

170
00:19:15,873 --> 00:19:17,750
I know the North and the South
made a deal,

171
00:19:17,833 --> 00:19:19,501
but we never know

172
00:19:20,044 --> 00:19:22,379
how things will turn out and when.

173
00:19:24,048 --> 00:19:25,299
You know that, right?

174
00:19:26,759 --> 00:19:27,801
Of course, ma'am.

175
00:19:27,885 --> 00:19:29,678
So the ANSP director's daughter…

176
00:19:32,806 --> 00:19:35,100
hid you in this dorm?

177
00:19:36,727 --> 00:19:37,770
Yes.

178
00:19:41,482 --> 00:19:45,194
Since you're indebted to her, it must
be bothering you. I understand that.

179
00:19:47,404 --> 00:19:51,116
But don't let
your personal feelings ruin our mission.

180
00:19:55,120 --> 00:19:57,665
I never had any personal feelings for her.

181
00:20:00,751 --> 00:20:02,378
I'm relieved to hear that.

182
00:20:12,388 --> 00:20:15,182
The hostage situation
hadn't been in the news all this time,

183
00:20:15,266 --> 00:20:17,142
but the news about it just broke out.

184
00:20:17,601 --> 00:20:19,311
And my face has been disclosed.

185
00:20:20,437 --> 00:20:24,108
Will we really be able
to go back alive in ten days?

186
00:20:26,986 --> 00:20:28,237
Comrade Lim Soo-ho.

187
00:20:29,571 --> 00:20:32,241
Are you worried about that
or doubting the party?

188
00:20:32,324 --> 00:20:34,451
I'm not doubting the party's orders.

189
00:20:35,202 --> 00:20:36,996
I just don't trust the ANSP.

190
00:20:37,579 --> 00:20:38,831
As I told you,

191
00:20:39,873 --> 00:20:42,793
last time we followed
the instructions and went out there,

192
00:20:42,876 --> 00:20:45,337
they sprayed us with bullets to kill us.

193
00:20:47,631 --> 00:20:51,093
If what you're saying is true, it means
they stabbed the party in the back.

194
00:20:51,176 --> 00:20:52,970
Would the party really have

195
00:20:53,762 --> 00:20:56,181
negotiated with such backstabbers again?

196
00:20:58,559 --> 00:20:59,476
Then…

197
00:21:01,520 --> 00:21:02,855
let me ask you one thing.

198
00:21:08,569 --> 00:21:10,070
Why in ten days?

199
00:21:11,780 --> 00:21:12,990
You seriously don't know?

200
00:21:13,866 --> 00:21:17,494
A veteran spy like you who's been
acting in covert all over Germany?

201
00:21:57,034 --> 00:21:58,160
That's a bomb, isn't it?

202
00:21:58,744 --> 00:22:02,873
They said they'd release more of us,
but aren't they going to just kill us all?

203
00:22:02,956 --> 00:22:05,292
There you go again.
Don't jump to conclusions.

204
00:22:05,876 --> 00:22:08,337
They wouldn't dare.
The army is surrounding this place.

205
00:22:10,422 --> 00:22:13,175
Wait. Where's Yeong-ro?

206
00:22:13,258 --> 00:22:15,677
What if they took only her somewhere safe?

207
00:22:16,178 --> 00:22:17,096
Keep it down.

208
00:22:17,179 --> 00:22:20,182
He took her out of here in secret.

209
00:22:20,766 --> 00:22:22,309
Stop talking nonsense.

210
00:22:24,353 --> 00:22:25,479
Get back to sleep.

211
00:22:25,854 --> 00:22:28,565
Even when they tried
to kill the doctor by the window,

212
00:22:28,649 --> 00:22:31,193
he desperately tried
to save Yeong-ro first.

213
00:22:31,276 --> 00:22:32,611
I saw it with my own eyes!

214
00:22:32,694 --> 00:22:33,821
Gye Bun-ok.

215
00:22:35,739 --> 00:22:37,699
I bet even if all of us here are killed,

216
00:22:37,783 --> 00:22:39,993
he'll still try to save Yeong-ro.

217
00:22:41,161 --> 00:22:42,579
It's already been two hours.

218
00:22:43,664 --> 00:22:45,165
They must've released her. Right?

219
00:22:45,249 --> 00:22:46,375
Of course not.

220
00:22:49,378 --> 00:22:50,879
She passed out.

221
00:22:51,547 --> 00:22:55,217
After hearing that her brother died during
an engagement with a Northern spy boat.

222
00:22:56,176 --> 00:22:57,636
Her brother died?

223
00:22:57,970 --> 00:22:59,513
I feel so bad for her.

224
00:22:59,596 --> 00:23:02,266
-Oh, no.
-Poor Yeong-ro.

225
00:23:14,194 --> 00:23:15,112
Honey.

226
00:23:15,195 --> 00:23:18,115
What are you doing here?
The guests are coming.

227
00:23:19,616 --> 00:23:21,118
It's all my fault.

228
00:23:22,202 --> 00:23:24,496
I'm the one who got him killed.

229
00:23:26,707 --> 00:23:28,959
That's not your fault.

230
00:23:29,543 --> 00:23:31,879
When you sent him to the front lines,

231
00:23:31,962 --> 00:23:35,757
you were in a crisis because of the Campus
Stabilization Act. You had no choice.

232
00:23:36,467 --> 00:23:38,802
On top of that, he protested
against the government.

233
00:23:38,886 --> 00:23:40,971
Very enthusiastically, at that.

234
00:23:41,054 --> 00:23:44,558
I was so worried
that you might get on Code 1's bad side.

235
00:23:47,978 --> 00:23:48,896
Honey.

236
00:23:50,063 --> 00:23:52,483
I know it's really hard for you,

237
00:23:52,566 --> 00:23:56,236
